{"id": 6775, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "3", "year": "2019", "session": "19M", "subtopic": "a-10-environmental-impact—heavy-metals", "title": "19M.3.HL.TZ2.8", "topic_id": "a", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Heavy metals are toxic even in very low concentrations.</span></p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Outline why heavy metals are toxic.</span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Determine the maximum concentration of lead(II) ions at 298 K in a solution in which the concentration of carbonate ions is maintained at 1.10 × 10<sup>−4</sup> mol dm<sup>−3</sup>. Use section 32 of the data booklet.</span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">State a method, other than precipitation, of removing heavy metal ions from solution.</span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><em>Any one of:</em><br/>disrupt endocrine system<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>compete for active sites of enzymes/cellular receptors<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>form complexes with/inhibit enzymes<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>denature proteins<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>change shape of active site  <strong>[✔]</strong><br/><br/>participate in redox reactions<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>disturb normal redox balance «in cells»  <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">initiate «free» radical reactions «in electron transfer»  <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">«<em>K<sub>sp</sub></em> = 7.40 × 10<sup>–14</sup>»<br/><em>K<sub>sp</sub></em> = [Pb<sup>2+</sup>][CO<sub>3</sub><sup>2–</sup>]  <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">[Pb<sup>2+</sup>] «= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{7.40 \\times {{10}^{ - 14}}}}{{1.10 \\times {{10}^{ - 4}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>7.40</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mn>10</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>14</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1.10</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mn>10</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 6.73 × 10<sup>–10</sup> «mol dm<sup>–3</sup>»  <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Note: </strong>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</span></em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><em>Any one of</em>:<br/>chelation «by EDTA/polydentate ligand anchored»  <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">ion exchange systems <strong style=\"color: #000000;font-family: Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;font-style: normal;font-variant: normal;font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: normal;text-align: left;text-decoration: none;text-indent: 0px;white-space: normal;\">[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">adsorption by «water» plants  <strong style=\"color: #000000;font-family: Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;font-style: normal;font-variant: normal;font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: normal;text-align: left;text-decoration: none;text-indent: 0px;white-space: normal;\">[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"color: #000000;font-family: Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: 14px;font-style: normal;font-variant: normal;font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: normal;text-align: left;text-decoration: none;text-indent: 0px;white-space: normal;\">Note: </strong>Accept “use of zeolites”.</span></em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>The candidates seemed to have difficulty in outlining why heavy metals are toxic.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>Majority of the candidates managed to get two marks in determining the maximum concentration of lead(II) ions using solubility product constant.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>This was not well answered by most of the candidates.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>"}